article.description: — Frank Mitchell scored 17 points as Canisius beat Western Kentucky 85-77 on Saturday.
article.headline: Canisius earns 85-77 win over Western Kentucky
article.linkText: Canisius earns 85-77 win over Western Kentucky
article.story: LAVAL, Quebec -- — Frank Mitchell scored 17 points as Canisius beat Western Kentucky 85-77 on Saturday. Mitchell also contributed 16 rebounds for the Golden Griffins (4-2). Siem Uijtendaal shot 3 for 9 (3 for 5 from 3-point range) and 6 of 6 from the free-throw line to add 15 points. Bryce Okpoh had 14 points and went 6 of 8 from the field. The Hilltoppers (4-2) were led by Don McHenry, who recorded 16 points. Babacar Faye added 15 points and 10 rebounds for Western Kentucky. Rodney Howard also had 15 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
